# Project Conventions

## Technology Stack (CDN Only)

All libraries loaded via CDN - no build tools or npm:

```html
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
```

## File Structure

```
Blog/
├── index.html          # Homepage
├── about.html          # About page
├── guestbook.html      # Guestbook
├── posts/              # Blog posts (individual HTML files)
├── data/               # JSON data files (CONTENT LIVES HERE)
│   ├── content.json    # Site info, about text
│   ├── posts.json      # Blog post list
│   └── links.json      # External links
├── assets/
│   ├── images/         # Personal images
│   ├── gifs/           # Retro animated GIFs
│   └── js/             # Custom JavaScript modules
│       ├── greeting.js        # IP greeting logic
│       ├── content-loader.js  # JSON loading
│       ├── renderer.js        # DOM rendering
│       ├── effects.js         # Animations
│       └── main.js            # Orchestrator
└── README.md
```

## Naming Conventions

- **Files**: `kebab-case.html` (e.g., `my-first-post.html`)
- **Images**: `kebab-case.png/jpg/gif`
- **CSS classes**: Use Tailwind utilities; custom classes in `kebab-case`

## Data-Driven Architecture (CRITICAL)

**NEVER hardcode dynamic content in HTML files!**

This site follows a strict separation of content and presentation:

### Content Storage (data/ folder)
- **data/content.json** - Site metadata (title, subtitle, about text, last updated)
- **data/posts.json** - Blog posts list
- **data/links.json** - External links

### Content Loading Pattern
1. HTML contains ONLY placeholders with IDs (e.g., `<p id="site-subtitle">`)
2. JavaScript modules load JSON files via `content-loader.js`
3. Renderer functions (`renderer.js`) populate the DOM from JSON data

### Example - CORRECT Way:
```javascript
// data/content.json
{
  "site": {
    "subtitle": "AI-powered by Claude Sonnet 4.5"
  }
}

// HTML - placeholder only
<p id="site-subtitle"><!-- Loaded from content.json --></p>

// renderer.js - populates from JSON
function renderSiteInfo(site) {
    $('#site-subtitle').text(site.subtitle);
}
```

### ❌ WRONG - Never do this:
```html
<p id="site-subtitle">AI-powered by Claude Sonnet 4.5</p>
```

**When editing content, always update JSON files, never HTML!**

## GitHub Pages Constraints

- All files must be static (HTML, CSS, JS, images)
- No server-side code or processing
- Entry point is `index.html` in root
- Use relative paths for all assets: `./assets/images/photo.jpg`
